{"id":"razor","term":"Razor","source":"International Standard Bible Encyclopaedia (James Orr ed., 1915)","html":"<p>ra'-zer (ta`ar, \"knife\" (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 6:5\">Nu 6:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 52:2\">Ps 52:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 7:20\">Isa 7:20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 5:1\">Eze 5:1</a>), morah, \"razor\" (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 13:5\">Jud 13:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 16:9\">16:17</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 1:11\">1Sa 1:11</a>)).</p><p>See BARBER; HAIR.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Numbers 6:5","Psalms 52:2","Isaiah 7:20","Ezekiel 5:1","Judges 13:5","Revelation 16:9","1 Samuel 1:11"]}